main event: A civilian reported observing an oval-shaped UFO and multiple pinkish light objects in Tempe, Arizona on September 7, 1965.
interesting points: The object emitted a high-pitched hum that caused a headache for the observer and a shock to his wife., The observation lasted for 8 minutes and involved one primary object and several others., The objects appeared to climb rapidly and headed towards the mountains., The sighting was visually confirmed by sober liquor store clerks residing in the area., No photographic evidence was collected despite the detailed reporting.
sighted object: one oval object and multiple pinkish light objects
witness description: civilian liquor store clerks, sober and self-assured
